The paper deals with signal recovery from noisy linear measurements, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The use of Expectation-Maximization and the variational interpretation of the algorithm suggest a machine learning (cs.LG) perspective. The paper also discusses the use of free energies, which is a concept from statistical physics (cs.SP). The simulations involve matrix manipulation, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with the joint recovery of the signal and learning of statistical parameters, which could be considered a problem in signal processing (cs.SI).
